close_reason: "Flexible deadline/date parser behavior shipped with +m and date-string support, docs/help parity updates, and full regression verification for existing users."
body: "Feature scope: parser update, command/help/docs alignment, and no-regression validation.\n\n## Detailed implementation plan\n\n1) Parser expansion and normalization in `src/core/shared/time.ts`\n   - Extend relative unit handling to support `+<n>m` month-relative deadlines using calendar-safe month math (Date#setUTCMonth).\n   - Add tolerant normalization for timestamp-like strings (e.g. `2026-03-31T13-59`, compact dates, and space-separated date/time) before Date.parse fallback.\n   - Keep canonical persistence behavior unchanged: all accepted values are written as ISO strings.\n\n2) Command-surface compatibility checks\n   - Ensure behavior is inherited automatically via existing `resolveIsoOrRelative` call sites in create/update/list/search/calendar/reminder/event parsing paths.\n   - Refresh usage/help strings where they currently imply a narrower contract than runtime behavior.\n\n3) Regression tests (new + existing invariants)\n   - Extend `tests/unit/determinism.spec.ts` with +m and flexible-date acceptance assertions.\n   - Add focused unit checks in list/search/create/update suites to validate new inputs and preserve prior behavior.\n   - Verify invalid junk still throws deterministic usage errors.\n\n4) Docs and contract alignment\n   - Update `README.md`, `PRD.md`, and `CHANGELOG.md` to document supported deadline/date formats and examples.\n   - Update CLI option descriptions and completion text so discoverability matches runtime behavior.\n\n5) Verification and closure evidence\n   - Run targeted unit tests for modified areas, then full `node scripts/run-tests.mjs test` and build validation.\n   - Record evidence in pm comments, close child tasks/feature/epic, and release claim."
